==English==

===Etymology===
From Old English, ''[[entredit]]'', ''[[enterdit]]''; or Old French, ''[[entredit]]'', ''[[interdit]]''; also from Latin, ''[[interdictum]]'', ''[[interdicere]]''--to interpose, prohibit; ''[[inter]]'' between + ''[[dicere]]'', to say.

===Verb===
{{en-noun}}

# {{transitive}} To [[forbid]] by church or legal [[sanction]].
# {{transitive}} To [[damage]], [[interrupt]] or destroy enemy lines of communication.
# {{transitive}} (''Roman Catholic'') to exclude a person or geographical area from participation in church [[symbolism]] and services.
# {{transitive}} To [[exclude]] from church [[sacrament]]s including [[burial]].

